text.tspan: Average per capita vegetable intake vs. minimum recommended
Countries shown in pink have an average per capita intake below 250g per person per day; countries in green are greater
than 250g. National and World Health Organization (WHO) recommendations tend to range between 200-250g per day.
Data source: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (2024)
Note: Figures represent average per capita supply of vegetables, which does not correct for waste at the household level.
